[
    {
        "content": "<p>Can we run the C preprocessor on <code>rust/bindgen_parameters</code> to allow certain parameters to depend on ifdefs?</p>",
        "id": 566379045,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767626703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I want to add a specific option only on <code>CONFIG_CFI</code></p>",
        "id": 566379471,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767626804
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In principle we could apply it always, but <code>--with-attribute-custom-enum</code> requires bindgen v0.71</p>",
        "id": 566379689,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767626851
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm thinking I can just gate <code>CONFIG_CFI</code> on bindgen v0.71</p>",
        "id": 566379972,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767626915
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or we can try bumping bindgen minimum version?</p>",
        "id": 566380051,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1767626936
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>works for me too</p>",
        "id": 566380150,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767626961
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Seems like debian is on 0.71.1 <a href=\"https://packages.debian.org/source/trixie/rust-bindgen-cli\">https://packages.debian.org/source/trixie/rust-bindgen-cli</a></p>",
        "id": 566380488,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1767627034
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Bindgen 0.71 is ~1 year old, and is available in Debian trixie. Using a feature that we need sounds like a reasonable motivation</p>",
        "id": 566380517,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1767627043
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See:<br>\n<a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260105-cfi-lru-status-v1-1-0b2401f7c5b2@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260105-cfi-lru-status-v1-1-0b2401f7c5b2@google.com/</a></p>",
        "id": 566390559,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767629660
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That patch doesn't actually bump min_tool_version?</p>",
        "id": 566393635,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1767630476
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No I didn't include that</p>",
        "id": 566393690,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767630488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I assumed a bunch of other stuff was required to carry out the bump</p>",
        "id": 566393756,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767630507
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And it probably requires a separate patch regardless</p>",
        "id": 566395588,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767630996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I sent a v2:<br>\n<a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260223-cfi-lru-status-v2-1-89c6448a63a4@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260223-cfi-lru-status-v2-1-89c6448a63a4@google.com/</a></p>",
        "id": 575723275,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1772010690
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess I'd like to hear from <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> whether you prefer to bump the bindgen minimum version, or that I implement <code>#ifdef</code> support in the bindgen parameters file to avoid that</p>",
        "id": 575723468,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1772010735
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I could take it after the bump of Rust and <code>bindgen</code> (I could send it as an use case, in fact, in the same series).</p>",
        "id": 575822233,
